### 🚀 DEPLOYMENT AUTOMATIZADO CON PARAMIKO

#### Script Python para SSH Deployment
```python
import paramiko
import time

client = paramiko.SSHClient()
client.set_missing_host_key_policy(paramiko.AutoAddPolicy())
client.connect(SERVER_IP, username='root', password=PASSWORD, timeout=10)

# 1. Backup BD
exec_cmd(client, f"pg_dump -U user db > backup_{timestamp}.sql")

# 2. Git pull
exec_cmd(client, "cd /opt/app && git pull origin main")

# 3. Install dependencies
exec_cmd(client, "cd /opt/app && npm install", timeout=600)

# 4. Build
exec_cmd(client, "cd /opt/app && npm run build", timeout=600)

# 5. Restart PM2
exec_cmd(client, "pm2 reload app-name")

# 6. Wait for warm-up
time.sleep(20)

# 7. Health check
status, output = exec_cmd(client, "curl -s http://localhost:3000/api/health")
assert '"status":"ok"' in output

client.close()
```

**Lecciones aprendidas**:
1. ✅ Paramiko está disponible en Cursor Agent Cloud
2. ✅ `time.sleep()` es CRÍTICO después de reload/restart (warm-up)
3. ✅ Health checks deben verificar response body, no solo status code
4. ✅ Timeout largo para `npm install` y `npm run build` (600s+)
5. ✅ Capturar exit_status Y output para debugging
6. ✅ Backup de BD antes de cada deployment (rollback)

